Here was evidence methods are sparking a response, with the last four days having now yielded successive clean sheets for the first time since mid-April. Porto top Champions League Group G after victory over Maccabi Tel Aviv Read more The teams destiny in Group G remains in their own hands, and there will be confidence the remaining home fixtures can be won, together with the trip to the whipping boys Maccabi Tel Aviv, to smooth passage into the knockout phase. The sense of satisfaction obtained here, though, should maintain the optimism generated fros welcome win over Aston Villa. said Mourinho. We are recovering some of that compactness, solidarity, effort, tactical discipline, qualities which are very important when you are not flying or playing with that confidence or flair, when your attacking players are not killing [opponents]. So in three days, two solid performances are good for us There was, inevitably, one gripe that needed to be aired.
